[{"id":4291131833,"node_id":"PRR_kwDOR8x2GM7_xXm5","user":{"login":"copilot-pull-request-reviewer[bot]","id":175728472,"node_id":"BOT_kgDOCnlnWA","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/in/946600?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/copilot-pull-request-reviewer%5Bbot%5D","html_url":"https://github.com/apps/copilot-pull-request-reviewer","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/copilot-pull-request-reviewer%5Bbot%5D/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/copilot-pull-request-reviewer%5Bbot%5D/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/copilot-pull-request-reviewer%5Bbot%5D/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/copilot-pull-request-reviewer%5Bbot%5D/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/copilot-pull-request-reviewer%5Bbot%5D/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/copilot-pull-request-reviewer%5Bbot%5D/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/copilot-pull-request-reviewer%5Bbot%5D/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/copilot-pull-request-reviewer%5Bbot%5D/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/copilot-pull-request-reviewer%5Bbot%5D/received_events","type":"Bot","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"## Pull request overview\n\nExtends semantic extraction context-budget controls to relationship mapping and entity-detail prompts to reduce prompt growth as catalogs expand.\n\n**Changes:**\n- Adds optional relationship relevance scoring, scene-scoped entity detail trimming, arc-aware compression, and prompt token metrics in `semantic_extraction.py`.\n- Adds `context_optimizations` flags to `config/llm.json`.\n- Documents the new optimization architecture and roadmap completion for #385.\n\n### Reviewed changes\n\nCopilot reviewed 4 out of 4 changed files in this pull request and generated 10 comments.\n\n| File | Description |\n| ---- | ----------- |\n| `tools/semantic_extraction.py` | Implements context optimization helpers, prompt formatting changes, relationship budgeting, and prompt metrics logging. |\n| `config/llm.json` | Adds optimization flags and changes default model/parallel worker settings. |\n| `docs/architecture.md` | Documents context-budget optimization behavior and prompt metrics. |\n| `docs/roadmap.md` | Marks #385 context-budget work as completed. |\n\n\n<details>\n<summary>Comments suppressed due to low confidence (1)</summary>\n\n**tools/semantic_extraction.py:1387**\n* For non-PC entities with `arc_aware_compression` enabled, this adds every relationship to the prior context with no count or relevance cap. When users enable all optimizations, the later `scene_scoped_detail` cap only trims the ΓÇ£Current Catalog EntryΓÇ¥ block, while this prior-state block can still inject the full relationship list and reintroduce the unbounded entity-detail growth the PR is meant to fix.\n```\n    elif rels and (is_pc or arc_aware):\n        # No arc data, or non-PC with arc_aware ΓÇö trim history to last 3 entries\n        compact_rels = []\n        for rel in rels:\n            trimmed = dict(rel)\n            if \"history\" in trimmed and isinstance(trimmed[\"history\"], list):\n                trimmed[\"history\"] = trimmed[\"history\"][-3:]\n            compact_rels.append(trimmed)\n        prior[\"relationships\"] = compact_rels\n```\n</details>\n\n","state":"COMMENTED","html_url":"https://github.com/daviburg/narrative-state-engine/pull/387#pullrequestreview-4291131833","pull_request_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/daviburg/narrative-state-engine/pulls/387","author_association":"NONE","_links":{"html":{"href":"https://github.com/daviburg/narrative-state-engine/pull/387#pullrequestreview-4291131833"},"pull_request":{"href":"https://api.github.com/repos/daviburg/narrative-state-engine/pulls/387"}},"submitted_at":"2026-05-14T15:21:22Z","commit_id":"714ee22130d7d365adeecb3d3bd8aa3dbc01e417"},{"id":4291161468,"node_id":"PRR_kwDOR8x2GM7_xe18","user":{"login":"daviburg","id":12040431,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyMDQwNDMx","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/12040431?u=fbee86a3b0623a272e7b0d2cc35950709fb3bca5&v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/daviburg","html_url":"https://github.com/daviburg","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daviburg/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daviburg/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daviburg/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daviburg/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daviburg/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daviburg/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daviburg/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daviburg/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daviburg/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"**[@reviewer]** REQUEST CHANGES\n\n## Blocking Issues\n\n### 1. _trim_entry_for_scene mention detection is non-functional\n\nFile: tools/semantic_extraction.py, lines 1504-1509\n\nThe function checks tid.lower() in text_lower where tid is a target_id like char-elder-malachar. Entity IDs never appear in raw DM text (DM writes 'Elder Malachar'). This makes the mention filter effectively a no-op, degrading to purely recency-based filtering.\n\nIn contrast, _collect_existing_relationships correctly uses _find_mentioned_entities() with name/alias word-boundary matching.\n\nFix: Pass a pre-computed mentioned_ids set from the caller (where catalogs are available), or pass catalogs and use find_entity_by_id + _find_mentioned_entities.\n\n### 2. No tests for new functions\n\nNone of the 5 new functions or 3 config flag paths have test coverage. Need at minimum: unit tests for _trim_entry_for_scene, _format_relationships_budgeted, _collect_existing_relationships with scoring, and prompt metric helpers.\n\n## Minor Issues\n\n3. Dead condition in tier-4 elif (line 1601) - both_mentioned is unreachable there.\n4. Final degradation in _format_relationships_budgeted has no budget check - may exceed budget if tier-1 alone overflows.\n\n## Strengths\n\nClean feature-flag design, good infrastructure reuse, well-designed tiered degradation, accurate doc updates.","state":"COMMENTED","html_url":"https://github.com/daviburg/narrative-state-engine/pull/387#pullrequestreview-4291161468","pull_request_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/daviburg/narrative-state-engine/pulls/387","author_association":"OWNER","_links":{"html":{"href":"https://github.com/daviburg/narrative-state-engine/pull/387#pullrequestreview-4291161468"},"pull_request":{"href":"https://api.github.com/repos/daviburg/narrative-state-engine/pulls/387"}},"submitted_at":"2026-05-14T15:25:26Z","commit_id":"714ee22130d7d365adeecb3d3bd8aa3dbc01e417"},{"id":4291444446,"node_id":"PRR_kwDOR8x2GM7_yj7e","user":{"login":"daviburg","id":12040431,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyMDQwNDMx","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/12040431?u=fbee86a3b0623a272e7b0d2cc35950709fb3bca5&v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/daviburg","html_url":"https://github.com/daviburg","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daviburg/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daviburg/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daviburg/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daviburg/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daviburg/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daviburg/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daviburg/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daviburg/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/daviburg/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":""